CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 24, 1961, pg. 18, reads: "Wee Winners - The bewildered winners of the recent baby contest sponsored by the Conference Workers of Homewood AME Zion Church are: Arthaniel E. Harris Jr., center, first prize winner; Rosetta Lloyd, left, who placed second, and Sandra Romaine Miller, who took third honors. The winner is the son of the host pastor.  Each is resting in arms of his chief promoter, 'Momie.' - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Three women, one on left wearing polka dot dress, holding three babies, including Rosetta Lloyd, Arthaniel E. Harris Jr., and Sandra Romaine Miller, at Homewood AME Zion Church, another version
